#: ../../docs/classes/class_meshinstance.rst:21
msgid ""
"MeshInstance is a node that takes a :ref:`Mesh <class_Mesh>` resource and"
" adds it to the current scenario by creating an instance of it. This is "
"the class most often used to get 3D geometry rendered and can be used to "
"instance a single :ref:`Mesh <class_Mesh>` in many places. This allows to"
" reuse geometry and save on resources. When a :ref:`Mesh <class_Mesh>` "
"has to be instanced more than thousands of times at close proximity, "
"consider using a :ref:`MultiMesh <class_MultiMesh>` in a "
":ref:`MultiMeshInstance <class_MultiMeshInstance>` instead."
msgstr ""

